The ^*BCavendish Invitational^*N was played last week at the ^*BMirage Hotel^*N in Las Vegas. The Cavendish consists of 2 events, a 3-session Swiss Teams followed by a 5-session IMP Pairs. The Cavendish is a very unique bridge tournament for several reasons, the main one being that, between these 2 events, well over 1 million dollars in prize money is available. Consequently many of the world's top partnerships and individual stars show up to play each May in Las Vegas.

Full coverage of the 2001 Cavendish Invitational, including online vugraph, is available through:

|cs|1|at|^-{ ^*Hwww.e-bridgemaster.com^*N }
^-
You can click on the yellow rectangle above to be taken directly to this web site in a new browser window. Unfortunately, it will cost you some money if you want to access the online vugraph. We consider this to be a serious setback as far as bridge is concerned. In our view the Cavendish is the most exciting bridge tournament of the year. The large cash prizes make this event interesting to members of the general public and it is a real shame that the tournament organizers, ^*BWorld Bridge Productions Inc.^*N, made the decision to make people pay in order to watch the online vugraph presentations (which have been free during the past 4 runnings of the Cavendish).

As usual, World Bridge Productions did a great job organizing the 2001 Cavendish, but we really think they missed the boat here. Let the tournament organizers know what you think by e-mailing:

|cs|2|at|^-{ ^*Bwbp@@thecavendish.com^*N } 

